            p.
              In the competition participated three fighters: <a href="../../girls/elena-vasileva2013Eng.html">Elena Vasilyeva</a>  (St. Petersburg, 5’6” / 132 lb); <a href="../../girls/kara-tellerEng.html"">Kara Teller</a>, Namazon Club’s newcomer (Moscow, 5’7” / 119 lb); <a href="../../girls/tais2013Eng.html">Tais</a>  (St. Petersburg, 5’7” / 130 lb). The tournament was held in a single round format. The girls eventually had to have two fights each. Each fight consisted of three 4 min rounds with 1 min rest between each round.
            h5 <u>The first fight</u> Elena Vasilyeva vs Kara Teller
            p.
              In the first two rounds the advantage was on the side of Elena, who was able to throw down Kara several times on the mat and had a lot of chances to finish her on the ground. Notice that Kara at the same time defended herself skillfully.
